              <DefinitionShort>(derivative of {L:ἐπερωτάω&lt;SDBG:ἐπερωτάω:000001&gt;}[b] ‘to ask for,’ {D:33.161}) that which is asked for</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>request</Gloss>
                <Gloss>appeal</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>It is also possible to interpret ἐπερώτημα in {S:06000302100030} as meaning ‘pledge’ or ‘promise,’ in which case it may be classified under {D:33.288}. Accordingly, the phrase συνειδήσεως ἀγαθῆς ἐπερώτημα εἰς θεόν may be rendered as ‘a promise made to God from a good conscience.’</Comments>
